<p>In korfball, shot percentage is tracked for each player. If John has a shot percentage of 25%, he scores on one out of every four goal attempts. John has two goal attempts. Below is a table, <em>X</em> is chance variable and the number of hits <em>X</em> on these two goal attempts can take the values 0, 1 or 2.</p>
<p>—— —— —— —— <em>X</em> 0 1 2 probability 0.56 0.38 0.06 —— —— —— ——</p>
<p>What is the expected score on two goal attempts? Round to two decimal places.</p>
</p>]]></text>
